metadata.name: Heroes of the revolt in Ukraine_01
metadata.description:
Hundreds of thousands of Ukrainian people from the whole country gathered together at Kiev's Independence Square on November 2014. Why? What made them to spend following nights in their tents in freezing cold winter and deploy lives on the barricades ...?
Ivan, 'I hope for Ukraine with free elections and no criminals in power. We need to be a democracy.' His demand is: 'The whole government and the president need to resign.'
